<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In typography, the part of a letter or other character consisting of a <a title="Bowl" href="Bowl">bowl</a> which serves as a flourisg, as in the bottom portion of the lowercase "g." See <a title="Letter Elements" href="Letter_Elements">Letter Elements</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In computing, a <em>loop</em> is any command or series of commands that endlessly repeats itself until the system is instructed to stop. 
</p>
<p id="l5">
In networking, a <em>loop</em> is used to refer to a network configuration in which each node is linked in series in a circular manner, data being set from dvice to device until it reaches the node it is addressed to. In such topologies, there is no central controller. 
</p>
